problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/boats-to-save-people/description/

Intuition
so when i looked at this prob lem i realized it is a 2 pointer problem and this can be solved easily if i sort the array , as the person with heaviest weight goes at the last of the list , then i can check if the person with heaviest weight + person with lightest weight can go on a same boat or not if not we assign the person with heaviest boat to an individual boat and then check person with lightest and second heaviest weight and so on .

Approach
to solve this we will be needing to sort the array , assign 2 pointers left , right at first and last index of the list , a variable count to count the number of boats required ,

we will check the condition till left is less than or equal to right , well why left = right becauswe there can be case when there is only one person i the list so left becomes right so this is handled by left <=. right , so we increase count += 1 in case there is only one element in list

we check if weight of heaviest person + weight of lightest perosn : people[left] + people[right] <= limit ; then we increase the count and move left pointer

we know that persons on right are the heaviest people so whenever people[left] + people[right] > limit , we only move right pointer as If the lightest person cannot fit with the heaviest person, then the heaviest person cannot fit with anyone.

we repeat this till left pointer either crosses right pointer or becomes equalt to it , which will give us the value of the least number of boats required

at the end we return the count , as number of boats required

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(nlogn)

Space complexity:
O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def numRescueBoats(self, people: List[int], limit: int) -> int:
        people.sort()
        left = 0
        right = len(people) - 1
        count = 0

        while left <= right:
            count += 1
            if people[left] + people[right] <= limit:
                left += 1
            right -= 1

        return count
